============================================================
Step 5: Physical interpretation of generators
============================================================
  Each generator is a direction in log-Pi space along which e* is preserved.
  Simultaneously rescaling the Pi groups along g leaves the keyhole physics invariant.

  Generator 1:
    Pi1 x exp(-0.667*eps), Pi2 x exp(+0.675*eps), Pi3 x exp(-0.315*eps)
    Meaning: increase Pi2 while decrease Pi1, decrease Pi3
             to keep Ke (and e*) unchanged

  Generator 2:
    Pi1 x exp(-0.647*eps), Pi2 x exp(-0.315*eps), Pi3 x exp(+0.694*eps)
    Meaning: increase Pi3 while decrease Pi1, decrease Pi2
             to keep Ke (and e*) unchanged


